    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d9744e86_efc568d6",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/darwinn/proto/darwinnpipe.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-19T19:11:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would take a look at go/required-fields-harmful and consider making fields optional.  Basically, required makes it more difficult to make changes later-- which would be a protocol-breaking change (changing the version number).  For minor changes, it may make more sense to deprecate a field and introduce a new one, doing an automatic upgrade when necessary.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 44,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "963f490817a83fc30a0ea2614d1dd8958fe25721",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "44c6269f_a0197d64",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/darwinn/proto/darwinnpipe.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 1368951
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-19T22:23:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s good to know. I have made all the fields optional and added checks with has_ for the optional fields. Out of curiosity, what happens if I try to access an optional field that does not exist?",
      "parentUuid": "d9744e86_efc568d6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 44,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "963f490817a83fc30a0ea2614d1dd8958fe25721",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f4c07022_2d1f45f3",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/darwinn/proto/darwinnpipe.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-20T01:27:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you access a field and it does not exist, you\u0027ll get a default value back.  For integers that\u0027s 0, for messages it\u0027s basically the message without any values set.",
      "parentUuid": "44c6269f_a0197d64",
      "range": {
